#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:26
#, no-c-format
msgid "Snapshots"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:28
#, no-c-format
msgid "Snapshots are mandatory"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:29
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As snapshots are crucial for the correct functioning of &slema;, do not "
"disable the feature, and ensure that the root partition is big enough to "
"store the snapshots."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:35
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When a snapshot is created, both the snapshot and the original point to the "
"same blocks in the file system. So, initially a snapshot does not occupy "
"additional disk space. If data in the original file system is modified, "
"changed data blocks are copied while the old data blocks are kept for the "
"snapshot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:42
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Snapshots always reside on the same partition or subvolume on which the "
"snapshot has been taken. It is not possible to store snapshots on a "
"different partition or subvolume. As a result, partitions containing "
"snapshots need to be larger than partitions which do not contain snapshots. "
"The exact amount depends strongly on the number of snapshots you keep and "
"the amount of data modifications. As a rule of thumb, give partitions twice "
"as much space as you normally would. To prevent disks from running out of "
"space, old snapshots are automatically cleaned up."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:52
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Snapshot that are known to be working properly are marked as "
"<emphasis>important</emphasis> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:57
#, no-c-format
msgid "Directories excluded from snapshots"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:58
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As some directories store user specific or volatile data, these directories "
"are excluded from snapshots:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:64
#, no-c-format
msgid "<filename>/home</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:66
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Contains users' data. Excluded so that the data will not be included in "
"snapshots and thus potentially overwritten by a rollback operation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:73
#, no-c-format
msgid "<filename>/root</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:75
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Contains root's data. Excluded so that the data will not be included in "
"snapshots and thus potentially overwritten by a rollback operation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:82
#, no-c-format
msgid "<filename>/opt</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:84
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Third-party products usually get installed to <filename>/opt</filename> . "
"Excluded so that these applications are not uninstalled during rollbacks."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:92
#, no-c-format
msgid "<filename>/srv</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:94
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Contains data for Web and FTP servers. Excluded in order to avoid data loss "
"on rollbacks."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:101
#, no-c-format
msgid "<filename>/usr/local</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:103
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This directory is used when manually installing software. It is excluded to "
"avoid uninstalling these installations on rollbacks."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:110
#, no-c-format
msgid "<filename>/var</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:112
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This directory contains many variable files, including logs, temporary "
"caches, third-party products in <filename>/var/opt</filename> , and is the "
"default location for virtual machine images and databases. Therefore, a "
"separate subvolume is created with Copy-On-Write disabled, so as to exclude "
"all of this variable data from snapshots."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:122
#, no-c-format
msgid "<filename>/tmp</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:124
#, no-c-format
msgid "The directory contains temporary data."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:130
#, no-c-format
msgid "the architecture-specific <filename>/boot/grub2</filename> directory"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:132
#, no-c-format
msgid "Rollback of the boot loader binaries is not supported."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:140
#, no-c-format
msgid "Showing exclusive disk space used by snapshots"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:141
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Snapshots share data, for efficient use of storage space, so using ordinary "
"commands like <command>du</command> and <command>df</command> won't measure "
"used disk space accurately. When you want to free up disk space on Btrfs "
"with quotas enabled, you need to know how much exclusive disk space is used "
"by each snapshot, rather than shared space. The <command>btrfs</command> "
"command provides a view of space used by snapshots:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:149
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"&prompt.root;btrfs qgroup show -p /\n"
"qgroupid         rfer         excl parent  \n"
"--------         ----         ---- ------  \n"
"0/5          16.00KiB     16.00KiB ---     \n"
"[...]    \n"
"0/272         3.09GiB     14.23MiB 1/0     \n"
"0/273         3.11GiB    144.00KiB 1/0     \n"
"0/274         3.11GiB    112.00KiB 1/0     \n"
"0/275         3.11GiB    128.00KiB 1/0     \n"
"0/276         3.11GiB     80.00KiB 1/0     \n"
"0/277         3.11GiB    256.00KiB 1/0     \n"
"0/278         3.11GiB    112.00KiB 1/0     \n"
"0/279         3.12GiB     64.00KiB 1/0     \n"
"0/280         3.12GiB     16.00KiB 1/0     \n"
"1/0           3.33GiB    222.95MiB --- \n"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:166
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <literal>qgroupid</literal> column displays the identification number "
"for each subvolume, assigning a qgroup level/ID combination."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:170
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <literal>rfer</literal> column displays the total amount of data "
"referred to in the subvolume."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:174
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <literal>excl</literal> column displays the exclusive data in each "
"subvolume."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:178
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <literal>parent</literal> column shows the parent qgroup of the "
"subvolumes."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:182
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The final item, <literal>1/0</literal> , shows the totals for the parent "
"qgroup. In the above example, 222.95 MiB will be freed if all subvolumes are "
"removed. Run the following command to see which snapshots are associated "
"with each subvolume:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:188
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;btrfs subvolume list -st /"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:192
#, no-c-format
msgid "Administration using transactional updates"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:193
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&slema; was designed to use a read-only root file system. This means that "
"after the deployment is complete, you are not able to perform direct "
"modifications to the root file system, e.g. by using <command>zypper</"
"command> . Instead, &slem; introduces the concept of transactional updates "
"which enables you to modify your system and keep it up to date."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:201
#, no-c-format
msgid "The key features of transactional updates are the following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:206
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"They are atomic - the update is applied only if it completes successfully."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:211
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Changes are applied in a separate snapshot and so do not influence the "
"running system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:217
#, no-c-format
msgid "Changes can easily be rolled back."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:222
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each time you call the <command>transactional-update</command> command to "
"change your system&mdash;either to install a package, perform an update or "
"apply a patch&mdash;the following actions take place:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:228
#, no-c-format
msgid "Modifying the root file system"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:230
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A new read-write snapshot is created from your current root file system, or "
"from a snapshot that you specified."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:236
#, no-c-format
msgid "All changes are applied (updates, patches or package installation)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:241
#, no-c-format
msgid "The snapshot is switched back to read-only mode."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:246
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The new root file system snapshot is prepared, so that it will be active "
"after you reboot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:252
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After rebooting, the new root file system is set as the default snapshot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:256
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Bear in mind that without rebooting your system, the changes will not be "
"applied."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:264
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In case you do not reboot your machine before performing further changes, "
"the <command>transactional-update</command> command will create a new "
"snapshot from the current root file system. This means that you will end up "
"with several parallel snapshots, each including that particular change but "
"not changes from the other invocations of the command. After reboot, the "
"most recently created snapshot will be used as your new root file system, "
"and it will not include changes done in the previous snapshots."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:275
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>transactional-update</command> usage"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:276
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <command>transactional-update</command> command enables atomic "
"installation or removal of updates; updates are applied only if all of them "
"can be successfully installed. <command>transactional-update</command> "
"creates a snapshot of your system and use it to update the system. Later you "
"can restore this snapshot. All changes become active only after reboot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:283
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <command>transactional-update</command> command syntax is as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:286
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"transactional-update <option>[option]</option> "
"<replaceable>[general_command]</replaceable> <replaceable>[package_command]</"
"replaceable> <replaceable>standalone_command</replaceable>\n"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:290
#, no-c-format
msgid "Running <command>transactional-update</command> without arguments."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:291
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you do not specify any command or option while running the "
"<command>transactional-update</command> command, the system updates itself."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:297
#, no-c-format
msgid "Possible command parameters are described further."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:301
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>transactional-update</command> options"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:303
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>--interactive, -i</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:305
#, no-c-format
msgid "Can be used along with a package command to turn on interactive mode."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:311
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>--non-interactive, -n</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:313
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Can be used along with a package command to turn on non-interactive mode."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:320
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>--continue [<replaceable>number</replaceable>], -c</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:322
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <command>--continue</command> option is for making multiple changes to "
"an existing snapshot without rebooting."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:326
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The default <command>transactional-update</command> behavior is to create a "
"new snapshot from the current root file system. If you forget something, "
"such as installing a new package, you have to reboot to apply your previous "
"changes, run <command>transactional-update</command> again to install the "
"forgotten package, and reboot again. You cannot run the "
"<command>transactional-update</command> command multiple times without "
"rebooting to add more changes to the snapshot, because this will create "
"separate independent snapshots that do not include changes from the previous "
"snapshots."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:337
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the <command>--continue</command> option to make as many changes as you "
"want without rebooting. A separate snapshot is made each time, and each "
"snapshot contains all the changes you made in the previous snapshots, plus "
"your new changes. Repeat this process as many times as you want, and when "
"the final snapshot includes everything you want, reboot the system, and your "
"final snapshot becomes the new root file system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:346
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Another useful feature of the <command>--continue</command> option is you "
"may select any existing snapshot as the base for your new snapshot. The "
"following example demonstrates running <command>transactional-update</"
"command> to install a new package in a snapshot based on snapshot 13, and "
"then running it again to install another package:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:354
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;<command>transactional-update pkg install "
"<replaceable>package_1</replaceable></command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:355
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;<command>transactional-update --continue 13 pkg install "
"<replaceable>package_2</replaceable></command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:359
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>--no-selfupdate</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:361
#, no-c-format
msgid "Disables self updating of <command>transactional-update</command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:367
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>--drop-if-no-change, -d</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:369
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Discards the snapshot created by <command>transactional-update</command> if "
"there were no changes to the root file system. If there are some changes to "
"the <filename>/etc</filename> directory, those changes merged back to the "
"current file system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:378
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>--quiet</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:380
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <command>transactional-update</command> command will not output to "
"<literal>stdout</literal> ."
msgstr ""

