msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:744
#, no-c-format
msgid "Snapshots cleanup"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:745
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you run the command <command>transactional-update cleanup</command> , all "
"old snapshots without a cleanup algorithm will have one set. All important "
"snapshots are also marked. The command also removes all unreferenced (and "
"thus unused) <filename>/etc</filename> overlay directories in <filename>/var/"
"lib/overlay</filename> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:752
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The snapshots with the set <literal>number</literal> cleanup algorithm will "
"be deleted according to the rules configured in <filename>/etc/snapper/"
"configs/root</filename> by the following parameters:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:759
#, no-c-format
msgid "NUMBER_MIN_AGE"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:761
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Defines the minimum age of a snapshot (in seconds) that can be automatically "
"removed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:768
#, no-c-format
msgid "NUMBER_LIMIT/NUMBER_LIMIT_IMPORTANT"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:770
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Defines the maximum count of stored snapshots. The cleaning algorithms "
"delete snapshots above the specified maximum value, without taking the "
"snapshot and file system space into account. The algorithms also delete "
"snapshots above the minimum value until the limits for the snapshot and file "
"system are reached."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:782
#, no-c-format
msgid "System rollback"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:783
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"GRUB 2 enables booting from btrfs snapshots and thus allows you to use any "
"older functional snapshot in case that the new snapshot does not work "
"correctly."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:788
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When booting a snapshot, the parts of the file system included in the "
"snapshot are mounted read-only; all other file systems and parts that are "
"excluded from snapshots are mounted read-write and can be modified."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:794
#, no-c-format
msgid "Rolling back to a specific installation state"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:795
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An initial bootable snapshot is created at the end of the initial system "
"installation. You can go back to that state at any time by booting this "
"snapshot. The snapshot can be identified by the description <literal>after "
"installation</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:802
#, no-c-format
msgid "There are two methods how you can perform a system rollback."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:807
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"From a running system you can set the default snapshot, see more in <xref "
"linkend=\"proc-running-snapshot\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:813
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Especially in cases where the current snapshot is broken, you can boot to "
"the new snapshot and set it then default, for details refer to <xref linkend="
"\"proc-boot-snapshot\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:820
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In case your current snapshot is functional, you can use the following "
"procedure for system rollback."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:825
#, no-c-format
msgid "Rollback from a running system"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:827
#, no-c-format
msgid "Choose the snapshot that should be set as default, run:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:830
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;transactional-update status"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:831
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"to get a list of available snapshots. Note the number of the snapshot to be "
"set as default."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:837
#, no-c-format
msgid "Set the snapshot as the default by running:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:840
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;transactional-update rollback <replaceable>snapshot_number</"
"replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:841
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you omit the <replaceable>snapshot number</replaceable> , the current "
"snapshot will be set as default."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:847
#, no-c-format
msgid "Reboot your system to boot in to the new default snapshot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:852
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following procedure is used in case the current snapshot is broken and "
"you are not able to boot into it."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:857
#, no-c-format
msgid "Rollback to a working snapshot"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:859
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Reboot your system and select <literal>Start bootloader from a read-only "
"snapshot</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:865
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Choose a snapshot to boot. The snapshots are sorted according to the date of "
"creation, with the latest one at the top."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:871
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Log in to your system and check whether everything works as expected. Data "
"written to directories excluded from the snapshots will stay untouched."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:878
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the snapshot you booted into is not suitable for rollback, reboot your "
"system and choose another one."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:882
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the snapshot works as expected, you can perform rollback by running the "
"following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:886
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;<command>transactional-update rollback</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:887
#, no-c-format
msgid "And reboot afterwards."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:894
#, no-c-format
msgid "Managing automatic transactional updates"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:895
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Automatic updates are controlled by a <command>systemd.timer</command> that "
"runs once per day. This applies all updates, and informs "
"<command>rebootmgrd</command> that the machine should be rebooted. You may "
"adjust the time when the update runs, see systemd.timer(5) documentation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:901
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can disable automatic transactional updates with this command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:904
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;<command>systemctl --now disable transactional-update.timer</"
"command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:908
#, no-c-format
msgid "Health checker"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:909
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Health checker is a program delivered with &slema; that checks whether "
"services are running properly during booting of your system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:913
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"During the boot process, <literal>systemd</literal> calls Health checker, "
"which in turn calls its plugins. Each plugin checks a particular service or "
"condition. If each check passes, a status file ( <filename>/var/lib/misc/"
"health-checker.state</filename> ) is created. The status file marks the "
"current root file system as correct."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:920
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If any of the health checker plugins reports an error, the action taken "
"depends on a particular condition, as described below:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:926
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>The snapshot is booted for the first time.</emphasis>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:928
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the current snapshot is different from the last one that worked properly, "
"an automatic rollback to the last working snapshot is performed. This means "
"that the last change performed to the file system broke the snapshot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:937
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>The snapshot has already booted correctly in the past.</emphasis>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:939
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There could be just a temporary problem, and the system is rebooted "
"automatically."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:946
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>The reboot of a previously correctly booted snapshot has failed.</"
"emphasis>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:948
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If there was already a problem during boot and automatic reboot has been "
"triggered, but the problem still persists, then the system is kept running "
"to enable to the administrator to fix the problem. The services that are "
"tested by the health checker plugins are stopped if possible."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:958
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding custom plugins"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:959
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Health checker supports the addition of your own plugins to check services "
"during the boot process. Each plugin is a bash script that must fulfill the "
"following requirements:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:966
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Plugins are located within a specific directory&mdash; <filename>/usr/"
"libexec/health-checker</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:972
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The service that will be checked by the particular plugin must be defined in "
"the <literal>Unit</literal> section of the <filename>/usr/lib/systemd/system/"
"health-checker.service</filename> file. For example, the <literal>etcd</"
"literal> service is defined as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:978
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"[Unit]\n"
"...\n"
"After=etcd.service\n"
"...\n"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:986
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each plugin must have functions called <literal>run.checks</literal> and "
"<literal>stop_services</literal> defined. The <literal>run.checks</literal> "
"function checks whether a particular service has started properly. Bear in "
"mind that service that has not been enabled by systemd, should be ignored. "
"The function <literal>stop_services</literal> is called to stop the "
"particular service in case the service has not been started properly. You "
"can use the plugin template for your reference."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1001
#, no-c-format
msgid "&slema; administration using Cockpit"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1002
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Cockpit is a web-based graphical interface that enables you to manage your "
"&slema; deployments from one place. Cockpit is included in the delivered raw "
"images, or can be installed if you are installing your own instances "
"manually. For the Cockpit installation process refer to <xref linkend=\"sec-"
"settings-software\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1009
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In case Cockpit is not installed in your system. You can install it "
"additionally by running:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1013
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;transactional-update pkg install cockpit"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1014
#, no-c-format
msgid "After reboot, Cockpit will be available in your system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1017
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Before running Cockpit on you machine, you need to enable the cockpit socket "
"in systemd by running:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1021
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;systemctl enable --now cockpit.socket"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1022
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In case you have enabled the firewall, you also must open the firewall for "
"Cockpit as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1026
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;firewall-cmd --permanent --zone=public --add-service=cockpit"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1027
#, no-c-format
msgid "And then reload the firewall configuration by running:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1030
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;firewall-cmd --reload"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1031
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now you can access the Cockpit web interface by opening the following "
"address in your web browser:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1035
#, no-c-format
msgid "https://<replaceable>IP_ADDRESS_OF_MACHINE</replaceable>:9090"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1036
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A login screen opens. To login, use the same credentials as you use to login "
"to your machine via console or SSH."
